H1> Configuring the chatbox

P> The Chatbox is a small real-time message board. With a couple of options it can be made safe for any audience.

Q> What is the Replace Links section for?
A> You can convert any link entered in the chatbox to other text or to an image. This keeps the chatbox from overflowing with long URLs. To use an image, tick [b]Replace Links[/b] and in the box below enter `<img src="path_to_your_image" alt="" />` – every link will then render as that image.

Q> What's Wordwrap for?
A> If a user types a single very long word it can stretch the column the chatbox lives in. Setting Wordwrap to e.g. `40` forces words longer than 40 characters to wrap. Tune the value to match the column width of your active theme.

H1> Moderation

Q> My site is for all ages but someone keeps swearing in the chatbox – how can I stop it?
A> Open [b]Admin → Preferences[/b] and find the [b]Protection of minors[/b] options. Add the words you want to censor; they will be replaced site-wide with the text of your choice (for example `CENSORED!`).

WARN> The censor list is global – it affects news, comments, forums and the chatbox alike. Test with a single benign word first to confirm behaviour.
